Personal Information that we "Share," "Sell," or Use for "Targeted Advertising"
We disclose the following categories of personal information to third parties for the purpose of engaging in targeted advertising and other marketing activities, including to expand the reach and effectiveness of our own marketing campaigns, for example to help avoid duplicative advertising to you.  In some cases, this information may also be used for the third parties’ own marketing purposes. These activities are considered “sales,” “sharing,” or “targeted advertising” under certain state laws and you have the right to opt out of having your personal information used or disclosed for these purposes.
This
means that we share identifiers, such as your IP address or your mobile device's marketing identifier, with 3rd parties who help us categorize you and other consumers into audiences and then adjust the advertising you see based on characteristics of that audience so that ads are more relevant.  You may opt out of this sharing at any time; if you do opt out you will still see advertising, but we will not share your data for purposes of tailoring those ads to our understanding of your interests.
Certain state laws also provide you with the right to opt out of data processing that constitutes “profiling” for purposes of decisions that may have a legal or similar effect, such as hiring or issuance of credit.  Here, “profiling” means the use of a solely automated process to render a decision. REI does not currently engage in any such “profiling.”
See below
for details about opting out.
